text: Karakol Peak (, ) is a mountain in the Terskey Ala-too of the Tian Shan. It is located in the Issyk-Kul Region in east Kyrgyzstan. ==History== It was first climbed in 1937 by N. Popov, G. Beloglazov, V. Ratsek, and K.
